{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1761764198,"nonce":"IdCjogMYttATDElCB0uVda30/hY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7UopNb","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7413","origin":"github"},"title":"Add support for TAF format as alternative to MAF","message":"## Description\n\nEvaluate and potentially implement support for TAF (Transposed Alignment Format) in addition to MAF format for multiple alignments in Galaxy.\n\n## Background\n\nDuring architecture discussions (Oct 24, 2025 meeting), the team discussed whether to support TAF format alongside or instead of MAF format.\n\n### Format Comparison\n\n**MAF (Multiple Alignment Format):**\n- Current standard format\n- Reference-projected and single-coverage\n- Well-established tooling\n- Large file sizes for many-way alignments\n\n**TAF (Transposed Alignment Format):**\n- More efficient storage\n- Can be more compact than MAF\n- Requires new tooling or tool rewrites\n- Less widely adopted\n\n**HAL (Hierarchical Alignment format):**\n- Used by Cactus progressive alignment\n- Too slow for direct use\n- Can be converted to MAF/TAF\n\n## Current Decision\n\nFrom meeting notes:\n\u003e \"Maximilian Haeussler acknowledged that TAF is a viable storage format but would require rewriting existing tools unless basic MAF functionality is first established.\"\n\n**Strategy:** Establish MAF functionality first, then consider TAF\n\n## Proposed Approach\n\n### Phase 1: MAF (Current)\n- ✅ Wrap existing UCSC MAF tools\n- ✅ Establish local file caching\n- ✅ Create workflows using MAF\n\n### Phase 2: TAF Evaluation (This Issue)\n- [ ] Research TAF format benefits vs MAF\n- [ ] Evaluate storage savings for large alignments\n- [ ] Assess tool availability for TAF\n- [ ] Estimate effort required for TAF support\n- [ ] Survey user demand for TAF format\n\n### Phase 3: Implementation (If Justified)\n- [ ] Convert UCSC alignments to TAF\n- [ ] Store TAF files on Galaxy CVMFS\n- [ ] Develop or wrap TAF manipulation tools\n- [ ] Create TAF↔MAF conversion tools\n- [ ] Update workflows to support both formats\n\n## Storage Considerations\n\nAnton's suggestion from meeting:\n\u003e \"Converting existing UCSC alignments to TAF and storing them locally on Galaxy CVMFS, given their manageable number\"\n\nExample file sizes to consider:\n- hg38/multiz470way/maf: 5.8T\n- Could TAF reduce this significantly?\n\n## Questions to Answer\n\n1. What storage savings does TAF provide?\n2. Are there performant TAF tools available?\n3. Does Benedict (progressive cactus) actually use TAF?\n4. Would users benefit from TAF support?\n5. Can we convert between MAF and TAF easily?\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Research Phase\n- [ ] Contact Benedict Paten about TAF usage in Cactus\n- [ ] Survey UCSC team about TAF tools\n- [ ] Measure TAF vs MAF size for same alignments\n- [ ] Review TAF specification\n- [ ] Identify existing TAF tools\n\n### Decision Document\n- [ ] Create comparison document: MAF vs TAF vs HAL\n- [ ] Include storage, performance, tooling analysis\n- [ ] Make recommendation: MAF-only, MAF+TAF, or migration to TAF\n- [ ] Get feedback from stakeholders\n\n### If Proceeding with TAF\n- [ ] Create TAF tool wrappers\n- [ ] Set up TAF file storage\n- [ ] Create conversion workflows\n- [ ] Update documentation","files":null}]}